{
  "stem": "1502.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "So they would do the dirty work-- take the Jews and do the dirty work in Poland where the population collaborated with them because they were just this anti-Semitic as the Nazis, or worse.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "But in Western Europe, they had to act in a different way.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "What they did-- they created this Judenrat.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Judenrat, that committee, got together and they asked all the Jews to register with that Judenrat.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "They have to come, stay in line, and register, fill out the registration-- who they are, where they live, how many people they are, the address, the telephone number, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "If you did not register-- the Germans said if you did not register with the Judenrat, you'd be sent to a concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "You'll be punished.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the fear was great.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the great majority of Jews were standing in line to register with the Judenrat.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "A friend of mine-- his father decided not to register with the Judenrat.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were never caught, and they were never deported.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They survived the war because the Gestapo wouldn't know about them.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But 90-- I don't-- I would say 98% of the Jews, for fear, registered with the Judenrat.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No one knew the consequences.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so did we.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We registered.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Our whole entire family registered.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And after we registered, a short while later, the Judenrat sent out like a subpoena.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was a gray paper, which I still have.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it was-- the, the, the letterhead was from the military commander of Belgium in northern France that you are ordered to report to the camp in Mechelen at this and this date.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And you have to take along with you food for, for two weeks, and you shouldn't take any food that spoils.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
